						               													<description>Kock&amp;aacute;zat (Battle of Dice Armies) is a quick, fun 2 player asymmetrical fantasy skirmish game. Players select a tribe ( Humans, Elfs, Orks, Gnomes, Dwarves, Undead, Fire and Ice ) and assemble an army using different dice ( d4,d6,d8,d10 and d12 ). Dices will be the units that the player activates to move&amp;nbsp;on the square grid board or attack the opponent's units. You start the game with all your dice set to it's highest value ( e.g a d6 starts on 6 ).&amp;#10;During a standard game you have an army of 100 points - each die in your army uses points equal to its highest value - so 5 pieces of d10 will use 50 points.Each tribe consists of 5 cards, one for each type of dice - these cards define what actions you can take.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a player's turn he/she activates one group of dice ( by tapping the related card ), and performs 2 actions with each dice: Move, Attack, Rest and Special Action paying the cost of activation by reducing the dice's value. Whenever a dice's value reaches zero it is removed from the board. You can not activate a group again until you have activated all of your groups.&amp;#10;Some of the abilities will place status effects on a unit ( Bless, Curse, Burning, Shield, etc. ) - these are marked by putting colored discs under the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win the game by eliminating all of your opponents dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
